Name: DROP ZONE INDICATOR
Explanation: AN INDICATOR AS TO WHETHER A DROP ZONE IS PRIMARY OR ALTERNATE.

Name: BROADCAST GEOGRAPHICAL AREA
Explanation: A CODE INDICATING THE GEOGRAPHIC AREA SERVED BY THE BROADCAST.

Name: POINT ALPHABETIC IDENTIFIER
Explanation: ALPHABETIC IDENTIFIER TO INDICATE THE SEQUENCE OF THE POSITION ALONG THE SHIP'S TRACK.

Name: MCM BUOY SEQUENTIAL NUMBER
Explanation: THE LETTER DESIGNATOR TO INDICATE THE SEQUENCE OF THE MCM BUOY.

Name: MCM OPERATION SUFFIX
Explanation: SEE ATP-24, CHAPTER 1, SECTION III, PARAGRAPH 132.

Name: TBMF AREA TYPE
Explanation: PROVIDES THE TACTICAL BATTLE MANAGEMENT FUNCTION REQUIRED IN A SPECIFIC AREA.REFERENCE 1: COMAIRNORTH SUPPLAN 24600D CONSTANT EFFORT FOR THE NORTHERN REGION INTEGRATED AIR DEFENCE SYSTEM (NRIADS).REFERENCE 2: COMAIRSOUTH SUPPLAN 45600 "DECISIVE GUARDIAN" FOR THE SOUTHERN REGION INTEGRATED AIR DEFENCE SYSTEM (SRIADS).

Name: NAVIGATION AID ICAO CODE
Explanation: THE GENERIC IDENTIFIER USED FOR A NAVIGATIONAL AID ICAO CODE.

Name: NATO REGIONAL IDENTIFIER
Explanation: A DESIGNATOR ALLOCATED BY A NATO COMMANDER TO A SUBORDINATE CORPS.

Name: TACTICAL OBSTACLE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: A DESIGNATOR ALLOCATED BY A BRIGADE OR DIVISIONAL TROOPS COMMANDER TO UNIQUELY IDENTIFY AN OBSTACLE OF SUBORDINATE UNITS.

Name: MODE (PEACE, WAR, OR OTHER)
Explanation: THE FIELD FORMAT SHOWS WHETHER THE CONDITION APPLIED TO THE DATA GROUP IS PEACE, WAR OR OPERATIONS OTHER THAN WAR.

Name: SUFFIX (PLACE KEY)
Explanation: ALWAYS USED IN CONJUNCTION WITH A BE NUMBER, UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES A PLACE, INSTALLATION OR FACILITY. [REF: STANAG 2439, AINTP-3]

Name: LOCATION ECHELON DISPOSITION
Explanation: INDICATES RECOMMENDED DISPOSITION OF A PW FOLLOWING AN INTERROGATION.

Name: EMITTER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: PROVIDES THE UNIQUE IDENTIFIER OF AN EMITTER.

Name: FLEET ID
Explanation: NAVAL FLEET TO WHICH A UNIT IS ASSIGNED.

Name: ALPHABETIC IDENTIFIER, HOMEBASE OR STARTING POINT
ADVANCED LOGISTIC SUPPORT SITE COMMANDER IDENTIFIER
TASK AREA IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IDENTIFIES IF THE TARGET OF A RECONNAISSANCE MISSION IS AN AREA, A LINE, A STRIP OR A PIN POINT.

Name: ZONE AID COLOR
Explanation: THE COLOR OF A ZONE AID DEVICE

Name: NAVIGATIONAL TRACK IDENTIFIER
Explanation: A UNIQUE IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO WAYPOINTS ALONG THE ROUTE.
